SHIGELLOSIS - UK (ENGLAND): BACKGROUND
**************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Shigellosis - UK (England) 981201205851
Date: Wed, 02 Dec 1998 07:12:20 -0800
From: Stephen A. Berger, M.D. <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background information on shigellosis in England and Wales
were extracted from the GIDEON software program:
England and Wales reported 9,830 isolates of _Shigella sonnei_ in 1991.
Laboratory reports peaked in 1992, with over 17,000 reports of _S. sonnei_.

46 outbreaks of _Shigella sonnei_ infection (involving 847 patients) were
reported during 1992 to 1994; 6,312 total _Shigella_ isolates were
registered in 1994; 1,283 _S. sonnei_ in 1996; 1,465 _S. sonnei_ in 1997.

7,012 cases of 'dysentery' were reported in 1994; 4,651 in 1995; 2,332 in
1996; 2,275 in 1997.

Highest rates during 1995 and 1996 were reported in Northern and Yorkshire
regions (ca. 3.8 per 100,000).
--
Dr. Steve Berger
e-mail: mberger@post.tau.ac.il
